The '''A499 road''' is the major road of the [[Llŷn peninsula]] in [[North Wales]].

Its northern terminus is a roundabout with the [[A487 road|A487 trunk road]] between [[Llanwnda, Gwynedd|Llanwnda]] and [[Llandwrog]] {{nowrap|({{coord|53.0948|-4.2824|type:landmark_region:GB|display=inline|name=A499 road (northern end)}}).}} It then runs south-westerly along the northern coast of the peninsula, through [[Clynnog Fawr]] then turns inland crossing the peninsula to meet the southern coast at [[Pwllheli]], it then follows that southern coast to terminate at [[Abersoch]] {{nowrap|({{coord|52.8227|-4.5054|type:landmark_region:GB|display=inline|name=A499 road (southern end)}}).}}

The total length is 23.4 miles. At no point is it a trunk road, although the Welsh Assembly has considered upgrading its status.<ref name=trunk-gc>[http://www.gwynedd.gov.uk/ADNPwyllgorau/2007/Bwrdd%20y%20Cyngor/2007-03-13/english/07_01_Review%20of%20Trunk%20Roads.pdf Gwynedd Council response to the Welsh Assembly Government] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080623155411/http://www.gwynedd.gov.uk/ADNPwyllgorau/2007/Bwrdd%20y%20Cyngor/2007-03-13/english/07_01_Review%20of%20Trunk%20Roads.pdf |date=23 June 2008 }}</ref><ref name=trunk-wa>[http://new.wales.gov.uk/news/archivepress/enterprisepress/einpress2003/713470/?lang=en Welsh Assembly Government: Long-term review of strategic road network]</ref>

== Improvements ==

Work started in February 2008 to upgrade the road between [[Aberdesach]] and [[Llanaelhaearn]] and also bypass [[Clynnog Fawr]]. This work is expected to complete in Summer 2009.<ref name=gc-pr>[http://www.gwynedd.gov.uk/gwy_doc.asp?cat=5653&doc=19983 Gwynedd Council Press Release Nov 2007] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071126084208/http://www.gwynedd.gov.uk/gwy_doc.asp?cat=5653&doc=19983 |date=26 November 2007 }}</ref> Previous work in 2006/2007 had cleared the new route of trees and erected boundary fencing.

