{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} {{Use British English|date=September 2017}} {{Infobox official post |post = Governor of Anguilla |body = |nativename = |flag = |flagsize = 150px |flagcaption = |insignia = Coat of Arms of Anguilla.svg |insigniasize = 100px |insigniacaption = Coat of Arms of Anguilla |image = |imagesize = 150px |alt = |incumbent = [[Tim Foy]] |incumbentsince = 21 August 2017 |department = |style = [[His Excellency]] |member_of = |reports_to = |residence = [[Government House, Anguilla]] |seat = |nominator = |appointer = {{unbulleted list|[[Elizabeth II|Queen Elizabeth II]]|<small>as [[Queen of the United Kingdom]]</small>}} |appointer_qualified = |termlength = [[At Her Majesty's pleasure]] |termlength_qualified = |constituting_instrument = |precursor = |formation = 1982 |first = [[Charles Harry Godden|Charles Godden]] |last = |abolished = |succession = |deputy = |salary = |website = [http://gov.ai/ministry.php?id=4 Office of the Governor] }} [[Image:Flag of the Governor of Anguilla.svg|thumb|260px|right|Standard of the Governor of Anguilla]] {{Politics of Anguilla}}
The '''Governor of Anguilla''' is the representative of the [[British monarch|monarch]] [[British Overseas Territory]] of [[Anguilla]]. The Governor is appointed by the monarch on the advice of the [[British government]]. The Governor is the highest authority on Anguilla, but daily business is handled by local Anguillan elected officials.<ref name=nytimes>{{cite news|first=Joseph B. |last=Treaster |title=For Anguilla, Tie to London Is Prosperity |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1988/04/17/world/for-anguilla-tie-to-london-is-prosperity.html |work=[[New York Times]] |date=1988-04-17 |accessdate=2015-03-17}}</ref> The main role of the Governor is to appoint the [[Chief Minister of Anguilla]].
The Governor's official residence is [[Government House, Anguilla|Government House]] at Old Ta. The Governor has his own flag, the [[Union Flag]] [[Defacement (flag)|defaced]] with the [[Coat of Arms of Anguilla]].
The current Governor is [[Tim Foy]], who was sworn in on 21 August 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sxm-talks.com/the-daily-herald/new-governor-for-anguilla-welcomed-sworn-into-office/ |title=New Governor for Anguilla welcomed, sworn into office |date=22 August 2017 |website=SXM Talks |location=St Maarten / St Martin}}</ref>
==List of Governors of Anguilla== *1982–1983: Charles Henry Godden *1983–1987: Alastair Turner Baillie *1987–1989: [[Geoffrey Owen Whittaker]] *1989–1992: Brian George John Canty *1992–1995: Alan William Shave *1995–1996: Alan Norman Hoole *1996–2000: [[Robert Harris (Anguilla)|Robert Harris]] *2000–2004: [[Peter Johnstone (governor)|Peter Johnstone]] *2004–2006: [[Alan Huckle]] *2006–2009: [[Andrew George (diplomat)|Andrew George]] *2009–2013: [[Alistair Harrison]] *2013–2017: [[Christina Scott]] *2017–{{As of|2017|8|21|alt=present}}: [[Tim Foy]]
