{{short description|A submerged circular reef of volcanic origin in the Northern Mariana Islands}} {{Infobox Seamount | Name = Supply Reef | Depth = {{convert|-8|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | Height = | Map = | Map caption = | Photo = | Photo alt = | Photo caption = | Photo size = | Summit area = | Translation = | Language = | Pronunciation = [[Northern Mariana Islands]], United States | Location = | Group = | Coordinates = {{coord|20|08|N|145|6|E|type:mountain_region:US-MP}} | Country = | Type = [[Submarine volcano]] | Volcanic group = | Range = | Age = | Last activity = | Last eruption = September to December 1989 | Discovered = | Discovered by = | First visit = }}
'''Supply Reef''' is a submerged circular [[reef]] of volcanic origin in the [[Northern Mariana Islands]] chain, about {{Convert|10|km|mi|0}} NW of the [[Maug Islands]]. Presently this igneous [[seamount]] is roughly {{Convert|8|m|ft|0}} below the ocean's surface and about {{Convert|100|m|ft|-2|abbr=on}} in diameter.
